# M6 P07 Phase 5 — slope-momentum carries-onto-flat probe.
#
# The user's request, verbatim: "moving side to side ... gain momentum
# sliding down a slope and then run out from the bottom of the slope
# quicker." Phase 1.1 baked in the above-cap guard so input is a CAP
# (not a target): when v_in_dir >= vx_cap the run input does nothing,
# so slope-launched velocity > RUN_SPEED persists on the slope. This
# probe checks the slope → flat transition: does the slope-launched
# momentum carry onto the flat ground, and how fast does friction
# bleed it back toward RUN_SPEED?
#
# Aurora's west hill: 30° slope rising east from world (640, floor_y)
# to (1024, hill_peak_y). The peak is at y ≈ 2528 (H-11), the floor
# is at y ≈ 2752 (H-4). Spawning slightly above the peak gives the
# mech a settled start.
#
# Scenario: spawn at top, hold LEFT — mech slides down the slope
# with active input. Phase 1.1's above-cap guard should let
# slope-tangent gravity push vt_now well above RUN_SPEED while LEFT
# is held, then on flat ground the same above-cap guard keeps the
# input from undoing the excess; only contact-friction (0.92/tick
# tangential on flat) bleeds it down toward RUN_SPEED.

window 1280 720
seed 1 0
out build/shots/m6_movement_slope
map aurora
no_parallax
spawn_at 1020 2516
aim 100 2500

# (a) Settle.
at  30 shot settled

# (b) Hold LEFT — slide + active run down the slope.
at  40 press left
at  60 shot descent_t020
at  80 shot descent_t040
at 100 shot descent_t060
at 120 shot descent_t080
at 140 shot descent_t100
at 160 shot descent_t120

# (c) Keep holding LEFT after the slope ends (transition to flat).
#     If Phase 1.1's above-cap guard works on flat too, vx stays
#     above RUN_SPEED briefly; friction (0.92/tick tangential) drags
#     it back toward the RUN_SPEED cap.
at 200 shot flat_t160
at 240 shot flat_t200

# (d) Release; friction-decel to stop.
at 280 release left
at 320 shot stopped

contact_sheet sheet cols 4

at 380 end
